    "created_at": "2015-11-29T00:33:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-29T00:35:17Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> This is stupid.\n\nNo, this is changing a dice-roll-generated default value to a sensible one. It's not disabling `Acceleration`, it's setting a proper default to avoid side-effects like those that caused the issue to be opened in the first place. From there any weapon can set its own acceleration if it needs it.\n\nBut you are right, there are a lot more apparently random generated default values in that class. In any case, this is probably good enough to fix the issue for the release. We can do more fine tuning (and hopefully fixing those ridiculous defaults) and reintroducing acceleration to RA missiles, because it looks pretty good, for the next release.\n\nP.S.: We should make sure this doesn't regress anything in the 3 shipped mods before we merge it!\n"
  },
