    "created_at": "2015-11-29T04:55:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-29T08:31:02Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> I did a quick glampse in the missile yamls -__ this is really bad__. Most missiles does not override the LaunchSpeeds so they will stay varied, which means missiles might end up being launched with a low speed without catching up to their old speed.\n\nJust the TS/RA2/heightmap mods would have an issue with perma-slow missiles due to no acceleration. The minimum speed is only ever used with regards to heightmaps.\n\nPersonally I would want all the defaults to be for an accelerated missile, we'd need less duplication in yaml, and that's I think the end goal. Point of this patch was just to be a band-aid for prep (TS is not shipped there), so I'll need to retarget the merge branch with a new PR. We'd be following up on bleed with a more proper fix in the future.\n\n> Set the MaximumSpeed default to MaximumLaunchSpeed instead of disabling Acceleration for the effect.\n\nIf we go this route we'd make yaml additions instead of changing the info class default. I'm more in favor of this but opting for least effort if we can.\n"
  }
